
For web-services!!  You write callbacks and it can work with XMLRPC, JSON, REST, SOAP, AMF, etc..

http://drupal.org/project/services

Users have a certain number of points:

http://drupal.org/project/userpoints

Ubercart integration for userpoints (can pay for things with userpoints):

http://drupal.org/project/userpoints_ubercart

For inviting a friend:

http://drupal.org/project/invite

Messaging/Notifications -- Allows users to configure how they want notifications (e-mail, SMS, XMPP):

http://drupal.org/project/messaging
http://drupal.org/project/notifications

XMPP support for Drupal:

http://drupal.org/project/xmppframework

IM between users:

http://drupal.org/project/im

For "buddy lists" between users:

http://drupal.org/project/user_relationships

** Also, note that Ubercart can now do 6.x! **

http://drupal.org/project/ubercart

For enforcing unique nodes based on various fields:

http://drupal.org/project/unique_field

Command line admin for Drupal:

http://drupal.org/project/drush

Check out this for providing the "verified" entries:

http://drupal.org/project/content_moderation

